                @{" BelchCDROM v0.6b [REL 0] by Noisy Belch/LOGIC " link "Install"}

                                   S!X ONLY

       This Door is PROTECTED against the LAME /X.info or "COMPATIBLES"
        I DONT code Doors for other peoples MISTAKES or PD BBS SOFTWARE
@endnode
@node "Install"
Move everything to DOORS:BelchCDROM/
------------ cut into BBS.CMD --------------
*cdrom    XM030DOORS:BelchCDROM/BelchCDROM
*cd       XM030DOORS:BelchCDROM/BelchCDROM
-------------------- cut -------------------

*** Important: Make sure that the DIR and LIST commands work because
               BelchCDROM uses the internal Express Directory routine
               which is also available when you enter 5 as command...
               Make sure that the Directory routine isnt disabled
               somehow...

*** Important: BelchCDROM works only with the standart Workbench
               c:Info command which is also included in this archive

Now check through the @{" DOORS:BelchCDROM/CONFIG " link "CONFIG"} file
@endnode
@node "CONFIG"
[-CONF-]    ...The conference where the user should access the CD-ROM
[-DEVICES-] ...Enter here every @{" DEVICE " link "DEVICE"} the user needs
               to access ("[-DEVICES-]CD0: CD1: CD2: CD4:")

*** Important: Make sure there is a SPACE between every @{" DEVICE " link "DEVICE"} name

*** Hint: Of course all Variables are NOT case sensitive
@endnode
@node "DEVICE"
If you really dont know what devices are then try this in shell


New Shell process 5
5> assign devices     
                      
Devices:              
FIFO PIPE CD0 PRT RAM 
CON RAW SER PAR WB_2.X
DF0 DH2 DOORS DH1     
5>
@endnode
